  "prompt": "Which one is the best book of Chemistry for 12th ISC?",
  "response": "For **ISC Class 12 Chemistry**, the **best books** are those that align with the syllabus and provide in-depth explanations, practice problems, and clarity of concepts. Here are the top recommendations:\n\n### **1. ISC Chemistry Book by S.P. Singh**\n   - **Why it\u2019s good**: This is the **most recommended book for ISC Chemistry**. It strictly follows the ASISC (Association of Schools for the Indian School Certificate) syllabus and provides detailed explanations, solved examples, and practice questions.\n   - **Focus**: Theory, numericals, and conceptual clarity.\n   - **Best for**: Students aiming for high scores and a thorough understanding of the subject.\n\n### **2. Concise Inorganic Chemistry by J.D. Lee**\n   - **Why it\u2019s good**: This book is a **classic for inorganic chemistry**. It explains concepts in a detailed yet simple manner and is ideal for understanding the theoretical aspects of inorganic chemistry.\n   - **Focus**: Inorganic chemistry concepts.\n   - **Best for**: Students who want to strengthen their inorganic chemistry base.\n\n### **3. Organic Chemistry by Morrison and Boyd**\n   - **Why it\u2019s good**: This is the **best book for organic chemistry**. It provides a clear and logical explanation of organic reactions and mechanisms.\n   - **Focus**: Organic chemistry concepts and reactions.\n   - **Best for**: Students who want to master organic chemistry.\n\n### **4. Physical Chemistry by O.P. Tandon**\n   - **Why it\u2019s good**: This book is **highly recommended for physical chemistry**. It covers numerical problems and theoretical concepts in great detail.\n   - **Focus**: Physical chemistry numericals and theory.\n   - **Best for**: Students who want to excel in physical chemistry.\n\n### **5. ICSE Chemistry for Class 12 by Dr. P.B. Saxena**\n   - **Why it\u2019s good**: This book is tailored for ISC students and provides a good balance of theory and practical questions.\n   - **Focus**: General chemistry with a mix of all topics.\n   - **Best for**: Students looking for a comprehensive textbook.\n\n### **6. NCERT Chemistry (Class 11 and 12)**\n   - **Why it\u2019s good**: Though primarily designed for CBSE students, NCERT books are **excellent for fundamental concepts** and are often recommended for competitive exams like JEE and NEET.\n   - **Focus**: Basics and fundamentals.\n   - **Best for**: Students aiming to strengthen their basics.\n\n### **Additional Tips**:\n   - **Practice Past Year Papers**: Solving ISC past year papers helps understand the exam pattern and important topics.\n   - **Chapter-wise MCQs**: Use books like **ISC Chemistry Chapter-wise MCQs** for exam preparation.\n\n### **Best Choice**:\nFor ISC Class 12 Chemistry, **S.P. Singh\u2019s ISC Chemistry Book** is the most reliable and **best choice**. It is specifically designed for the ISC syllabus and covers all aspects of the subject comprehensively. Additionally, supplement it with **Morrison and Boyd** for organic chemistry and **O.P. Tandon** for physical chemistry for a well-rounded preparation.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
